  "prompt": "What does \"subject to availability\" mean?",
  "response": "\"Subject to availability\" is a phrase commonly used in various contexts, such as sales, services, bookings, and reservations. It means that the item, service, or opportunity being offered is not guaranteed to be available at all times and depends on current stock, demand, or other conditions. Essentially, the availability of the item or service is contingent on whether it is in stock or accessible at the time of inquiry or purchase. For example, if a hotel room is advertised as \"subject to availability,\" it means that you can book the room only if it is still available at the time you make the reservation.",
